Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan and bring to the boil. When boiling, add a @salt{pinch}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat and pop a lid on the pan. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim and grate the @carrot{1}(grated) (no need to peel). Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}. Zest and half the @lime{1}. Pop the carrot and peanuts into a #bowl. Add the juice from half the lime, a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Add a @?sugar{pinch}. Mix to combine then set aside.

Reserving the juice, drain the @pineapple rings{1} using a #sieve. Chop the pineapple into 1cm dice. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Pop the pineapple into another small #bowl, along with the remaining lime juice, half the coriander and a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the salsa and mix. Set to one side.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(thinly sliced). Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. Once hot, add the onion and the @beef strips{240%g}. Season with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir-fry until browned all over, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #bowl and return the pan to the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The steak strips are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Pour the @soy sauce{25%ml} and 3 tbsp of the reserved pineapple juice per person into the hot #frying pan. Bring to the boil and reduce until thickened and glossy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Return the steak and onion to the pan and remove from the heat. Toss to coat the steak strips in the sauce.

When you are ready to serve, fluff up the rice with a #fork and mix through the lime zest and remaining coriander. Serve the rice in #bowls with the Hawaiian steak on one side, the carrot salad on the other side and the pineapple salsa on top. Enjoy!

> A top tip from our chefs is not to overcrowd the pan when stir-frying your steak. Keep the oil nice and hot and cook the steak in batches to stop the meat from stewing.